{"File":"/home/lowcache/.nix-config/dots/gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/8a4950ce-a9a5-4e7f-a33b-5346cc3bf527/.system_generated/logs/transcript_full.jsonl","LineNumber":400,"LineContent":"{\"step_index\":402,\"source\":\"MODEL\",\"type\":\"PLANNER_RESPONSE\",\"status\":\"DONE\",\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:12:22Z\",\"content\":\"### Repository Directory Topology\\n\\nThe unified repository (`~/.nix-config`) is cloned onto both the laptop and the phone, functioning as a single source of truth. The repository directory structure separates configurations by target environment:\\n\\n```\\n~/.nix-config/\\n├── flake.nix                  # Unified entrypoint defining outputs for both platforms\\n├── nixos/                     # System-level configurations (Desktop-only)\\n│   ├── configuration.nix      # Custom kernel, Lanzaboote, MicroVMs, systemd\\n│   └── hardware-configuration.nix\\n├── nix-on-droid/              # System-level configurations (Phone-only)\\n│   └── configuration.nix      # Proot parameters, user shell definitions\\n└── home/                      # User-level configurations\\n    ├── common.nix             # Platform-agnostic settings (shared)\\n    ├── shell-common.nix       # Shared Fish settings, micro config, git profiles\\n    ├── desktop.nix            # Laptop-specific Home Manager profile\\n    ├── pkgs.nix               # Desktop packages (Hyprland, GUI)\\n    ├── session.nix            # Desktop session variables and cursors\\n    ├── persist.nix            # Desktop impermanence storage mappings\\n    ├── brave.nix              # Desktop Brave browser configurations\\n    └── droid.nix              # Phone-specific Home Manager profile (CLI, Shizuku)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Evaluation and Target Architectural Mapping\\n\\nEvaluation targets, system profiles, and runtime bounds diverge at the flake entrypoint:\\n\\n| Parameter | Laptop Host (`nondeus`) | Samsung S26 Ultra (`default`) |\\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\\n| **System Profile** | NixOS System | Nix-on-Droid (`proot` container) |\\n| **Architecture** | `x86_64-linux` | `aarch64-linux` |\\n| **Kernel \u0026 Core** | Custom CachyOS, Systemd, Lanzaboote | Shared Android Linux Kernel |\\n| **User Space Paths** | `/home/nondeus` | `/data/data/com.tuxera.nixondroid/files/home` |\\n| **User Configuration** | `home/desktop.nix` | `home/droid.nix` |\\n| **Evaluation Method** | Pure (`nixos-rebuild switch`) | Impure (`nix-on-droid switch --impure`) |\\n| **State Persistence** | Declarative Ephemeral Root (`/persist`) | Standard Android application directories |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### The Common Core (Shared Configurations)\\n\\nThe following configurations evaluate identically on both the laptop and the S26 Ultra:\\n\\n*   **Core Text Editor (Micro)**: Identical keybindings, tab settings, Dracula color palette, automated formatting using `nixpkgs-fmt`, and language server configurations (`nil` LSP) for syntax validation.\\n*   **Shell Core (Fish)**: General terminal interaction rules, directory navigation aliases (`..`, `...`), automatic directories list (`ls` wrapper for `eza`), archive extraction helper scripts (`extract`), and custom file renaming utilities (`rmspcs`).\\n*   **Git Identity**: Global user profile name, email configuration, and Git Large File Storage (LFS) support.\\n*   **Directory Environment Configuration (Direnv)**: Automatically loading isolated dependency layers when entering workspaces, matching system path configurations dynamically.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Target-Specific Specializations\\n\\n#### Laptop Specialization\\n*   **System-level**: MicroVM configurations (`net-gate` tor gateway), custom systemd daemons (Open WebUI persistent mounts), Lanzaboote Secure Boot certificates, and AMD/NVIDIA hybrid graphics configurations.\\n*   **User-level**: Hyprland desktop environment, Quickshell terminal styling, Waypaper wallpaper management, desktop GTK themes, Wayland compatibility for electron apps, and state persistence bindings targeting `/persist`.\\n\\n#### Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra Specialization\\n*   **System-level**: Direct terminal execution hooks running Fish under Android's unprivileged proot interface.\\n*   **User-level**: Integration of the Shizuku API wrapper (`rish`) in user path directories to enable elevated system commands. Command-line-only system monitors (`htop`), directory utilities (`fzf`, `ripgrep`), and Android energy-saving policy exemptions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Runtime Integration Flows\\n\\nThe operational connection between both nodes creates a unified terminal environment:\\n\\n```\\n  +-----------------------+                    +-----------------------+\\n  |    Laptop Host        |                    |   Samsung S26 Ultra   |\\n  |    (x86_64-linux)     |                    |    (aarch64-linux)    |\\n  +-----------------------+                    +-----------------------+\\n  |  - Hyprland Desktop   |                    |  - Terminal Environment|\\n  |  - CachyOS Systemd    |                    |  - Shizuku ADB Shell   |\\n  |  - Wayland Clipboard  | \u003c--- Tailscale ---\u003e|  - Background Daemons |\\n  |  - Shared Git Config  |                    |  - Shared Git Config  |\\n  +-----------------------+                    +-----------------------+\\n```\\n\\n*   **Dev Workspace Portability**: When you clone a programming repository onto either device, the local `direnv` evaluates the flake's specific architecture packages. Code completions, development servers, and database modules run natively on `aarch64-linux` on the phone, replicating the laptop environment.\\n*   **Exempting Power Restrictions**: On terminal startup, a Nix-on-Droid shell hook leverages the local Shizuku binary to whitelist the terminal process from device idling and adjust the phantom process limit. This ensures database servers or SSH daemons run in the background without operating system termination.\\n*   **Encrypted Secrets Handling**: Sops-nix targets GPG key schemes on both systems. Encrypted da