To make the desktop entries resilient to username rotations while remaining compliant with the XDG specification, choose one of the following methods:

### Option 1: Standard Shell Wrapper (Zero configuration changes)
Although XDG desktop launchers do not parse `$HOME`, they can launch a shell (`sh`), which *does* expand variables. Using `exec` replaces the shell process immediately, introducing zero system overhead.

Modify the `.desktop` files to use the following structure:

1. **[antigravity.desktop](file:///home/lowcache/.local/share/applications/antigravity.desktop)**:
   ```ini
   Exec=sh -c "exec ~/.local/bin/antigravity"
   ```
2. **[antigravity-ide.desktop](file:///home/lowcache/.local/share/applications/antigravity-ide.desktop)**:
   ```ini
   Exec=sh -c "exec ~/.local/bin/antigravity-ide"
   Icon=sh -c "exec ~/.local/share/Antigravity IDE/resources/app/resources/linux/code.png"
   ```
   *(Note: The XDG specification does not support shell wrapper commands in the `Icon` field; the icon path must remain absolute or be resolved via a system icon theme).*

---

### Option 2: Declarative Home Manager Generation (Recommended Nix Way)
You can configure Home Manager to generate these `.desktop` entries dynamically. This ensures that the generated paths are absolute, but compiled automatically using `${config.home.homeDirectory}` based on your active user environment.

Add the following to your Home Manager configuration (e.g., [home/default.nix](file:///home/lowcache/.nix-config/home/default.nix)):

```nix
  xdg.desktopEntries = {
    antigravity = {
      name = "Antigravity";
      comment = "Antigravity application";
      exec = "${config.home.homeDirectory}/.local/bin/antigravity";
      icon = "system-run";
      type = "Application";
      categories = [ "Utility" "Development" ];
      mimeType = [ "x-scheme-handler/antigravity" ];
    };
    antigravity-ide = {
      name = "Antigravity IDE";
      comment = "Antigravity Integrated Development Environment";
      exec = "${config.home.homeDirectory}/.local/bin/antigravity-ide";
      icon = "${config.home.homeDirectory}/.local/share/Antigravity IDE/resources/app/resources/linux/code.png";
      type = "Application";
      categories = [ "Development" "IDE" ];
    };
  };
```

This method eliminates hardcoded paths and generates optimized, fully compliant files dynamically during `nixos-rebuild switch`.

